WEBVTT

00:03.170 --> 00:04.160
- Previously on Being Human:

00:04.230 --> 00:05.698
- I'm like you.
I'm a wolf,

00:05.770 --> 00:06.840
- Push!

00:06.900 --> 00:08.129
(Caroline screaming)

00:08.200 --> 00:10.009
- She's perfect.

00:11.740 --> 00:14.380
- What do you think?
- How did you pull it off? Club?

00:14.440 --> 00:16.078
Getting the
vampires in line?

00:16.149 --> 00:18.403
- Someone like me can be
a pretty smart fighter.

00:20.650 --> 00:22.414
- You can change
the way you look?

00:22.490 --> 00:24.117
- I can control what people see.

00:24.190 --> 00:26.557
- Oh my God!

00:26.620 --> 00:29.282
The house! The '70s!

00:29.360 --> 00:30.759
I'm travelling through time.

00:30.830 --> 00:32.855
- If you really love this girl,

00:32.930 --> 00:35.228
the best thing you can do
is break up with her.

00:35.300 --> 00:37.223
- I have been lying to you.

00:37.300 --> 00:40.099
Because I am a vampire.

00:41.200 --> 00:43.032
(Laughing)

00:44.570 --> 00:47.335
(Laughing)

00:47.410 --> 00:49.606
- Oh! Oh my God, your face!

00:49.680 --> 00:50.772
(Laughing)

00:50.850 --> 00:53.114
- You're laughing, all right.

00:53.180 --> 00:54.670
I wasn't exactly
expecting this.

00:54.750 --> 00:57.412
- I didn't expect you

00:57.490 --> 00:59.254
to tell me that you're Dracula.

00:59.320 --> 01:01.254
- Kat, I'm telling
you the truth.

01:05.290 --> 01:07.395
- Oh, you really believe this.

01:07.460 --> 01:09.667
- It's not a question
of what I believe.

01:09.730 --> 01:11.289
It's a question of what is.

01:11.370 --> 01:12.269
I am a vampire.

01:13.740 --> 01:15.333
- OK.

01:17.510 --> 01:19.569
- So--50, you can
ask me questions. You--

01:19.640 --> 01:21.130
Say something.
Say anything.

01:21.210 --> 01:23.144
- It's gonna be OK.

01:23.210 --> 01:25.349
We're gonna get help.

01:25.410 --> 01:26.775
- Help...

01:26.850 --> 01:28.909
- We're gonna talk
to a professional and--

01:28.980 --> 01:31.483
- OK, no more talking.
Listen, listen, listen...

01:33.460 --> 01:34.484
(Inhaling deeply)

01:34.560 --> 01:35.618
What do you hear?

01:35.690 --> 01:37.488
- Nothing.
I don't hear anything.

01:40.730 --> 01:42.494
I don't hear your heartbeat.

01:43.830 --> 01:45.559
That's because
I don't have one.

01:50.970 --> 01:52.404
- No, there's gotta be--

01:52.480 --> 01:54.300
- Kat, OK. Kat,
Kat, listen to me.

01:54.380 --> 01:55.529
I'm gonna do something...

01:56.780 --> 01:59.715
and I just need
you to trust me, OK?

02:00.820 --> 02:02.584
Trust me.

02:08.020 --> 02:10.158
Kat, it's still me.

02:18.870 --> 02:22.238
- (Kat): Have you killed people?
Are you a killer?

02:22.310 --> 02:23.732
(Sobbing)

02:23.810 --> 02:25.460
- I love you.

02:25.540 --> 02:26.871
- How can I trust you?

02:28.680 --> 02:30.307
(Paper rustling)

02:30.380 --> 02:31.302
How many?

02:35.020 --> 02:37.990
Jeff, my ex, went missing
right after you met him.

02:38.050 --> 02:40.917
- Oh God, Kat, no!
No, no, no. No.

02:40.990 --> 02:43.630
I don't do that anymore.
That's not me anymore.

02:46.830 --> 02:48.798
That isn't gonna
do you any good.

02:48.860 --> 02:50.669
- Who else knows
what you are?

02:50.730 --> 02:52.835
- Just the people
I live with, Kat,

02:52.900 --> 02:55.232
just Josh and Nora and Sally.

02:55.300 --> 02:56.699
- Who's Sally?

02:57.910 --> 02:59.605
(Sighing)

02:59.680 --> 03:03.002
** Tl meet with him... *

03:03.080 --> 03:04.969
- Tell me what you're feeling.

03:05.050 --> 03:06.575
* The last time... *

03:06.650 --> 03:08.243
You can be honest with me.

03:10.550 --> 03:12.757
* The last time... *

03:12.820 --> 03:14.458
- Scared.

03:16.330 --> 03:17.525
I feel scared.

03:17.590 --> 03:18.523
- That's...

03:19.600 --> 03:20.795
That's normal.

03:20.860 --> 03:22.692
It's a crazy
situation.

03:22.770 --> 03:24.898
- I'm not scared
of the situation.

03:24.970 --> 03:26.836
* Dance like this... *

03:26.900 --> 03:28.595
It's you.

03:29.770 --> 03:31.260
I'm scared of you.

03:32.880 --> 03:34.507
- OK.

03:36.610 --> 03:39.409
Um, if you need me
to go, I can--

03:39.480 --> 03:41.471
- Yes, please go.

03:41.550 --> 03:44.941
* A golden thread I spin *

03:46.660 --> 03:51.427
* I dance like this... *

03:51.490 --> 03:53.549
- For how long?

03:55.060 --> 03:57.324
* For me... *

03:57.400 --> 03:58.561
Um...

04:00.800 --> 04:02.461
OK.

04:02.540 --> 04:06.306
* Whoa *

04:07.610 --> 04:09.442
* Whoa *

04:13.580 --> 04:15.275
* Whoa *

04:19.420 --> 04:23.926
* I'll meet with him *

04:25.430 --> 04:27.797
* The last time **

04:31.970 --> 04:33.631
- (Nora and Andrew): Hi!

04:33.700 --> 04:36.465
- Thanks for stopping by!
Come on in!

04:36.540 --> 04:38.429
- We wanted to check
up on your guys!

04:38.510 --> 04:40.103
See how baby April's doing.

04:40.180 --> 04:42.808
See if she's gotten any cuter,
not that that's possible.

04:42.880 --> 04:44.575
- AR

04:44.650 --> 04:47.017
- Josh, Nora, this
is Mark and Wendy.

04:47.080 --> 04:48.969
- We have heard
a lot about you guys.

04:49.050 --> 04:51.587
- Nice to meet you!
- No, no, bring it in for a hug.

04:51.650 --> 04:52.856
Come on, buddy!

04:52.920 --> 04:54.081
So good to meet you guys!

04:54.160 --> 04:55.855
There's nothing
to worry about, buddy.

04:55.920 --> 04:57.979
We're Howlers like you.

04:58.060 --> 04:59.926
- Mark and Wendy
were attacked with us.

05:00.000 --> 05:01.752
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- Wow!

05:01.830 --> 05:03.696
- There's nothing
to be sorry about.

05:03.770 --> 05:05.067
There's worse things to be.

05:05.130 --> 05:06.768
(Giggling)

05:06.840 --> 05:08.990
- It's weird though, when
we stumble upon each other.

05:09.070 --> 05:11.129
- Do you stumble
on a lot of us?

05:11.210 --> 05:12.700
- I don't stumble.

05:12.780 --> 05:14.430
I look for
people like us.

05:14.510 --> 05:15.807
We feel it's important

05:15.880 --> 05:17.769
to have a sense
of community.

05:17.850 --> 05:19.443
- No, not always.

05:19.520 --> 05:21.648
- Where'd you find this guy?

05:21.720 --> 05:22.744
(Both laughing)

05:22.820 --> 05:24.140
(Laughing)

05:24.220 --> 05:25.642
- We gotta go.
- Yes, yeah.

05:25.720 --> 05:27.814
- It was so great
seeing the baby!

05:27.890 --> 05:29.380
It was lovely
to meet you guys.

05:29.460 --> 05:30.552
- You too!

05:30.630 --> 05:31.756
- Bye, guys!

05:31.830 --> 05:32.922
- Bye!
- Thanks again!

05:33.000 --> 05:34.490
We'll see you around!
- Sure.

05:34.560 --> 05:35.891
- Let me see her!

05:35.960 --> 05:38.167
Oh my God,
she's so big!

05:38.230 --> 05:40.938
- So, I know Mark's
a little intense,

05:41.000 --> 05:43.503
but he's actually
really sweet.

05:43.570 --> 05:44.731
- Yes.

05:44.810 --> 05:46.471
- Your baby is perfect!
- I know!

05:46.540 --> 05:48.770
- Look at her, oh my gosh!

05:48.840 --> 05:50.569
Uh, here, we got you...

05:50.650 --> 05:51.947
- Open it!

05:52.010 --> 05:54.047
- It's just kind of
a supply grab bag.

05:54.120 --> 05:56.817
- Put together by 2 people
who have no children,

05:56.890 --> 05:58.187
so it's fairly half-assed.

05:58.250 --> 05:59.911
- Why don't you open it?

05:59.990 --> 06:04.086
- Here we go, sweetie. There.

06:04.160 --> 06:06.026
You really didn't
need to do this.

06:06.090 --> 06:08.092
- Oh, we wanted to!

06:09.500 --> 06:12.162
- Oh my gosh!

06:12.230 --> 06:13.493
- A little wolf on it.

06:13.570 --> 06:15.436
- This is adorable!

06:15.500 --> 06:19.539
Thank you so much!
You really... This is...

06:19.610 --> 06:21.169
- Are you OK?

06:21.240 --> 06:24.505
- Things are just
happening really fast.

06:25.680 --> 06:28.115
Just a little...
overwhelmed.

06:28.180 --> 06:30.444
- That's totally
understandable.

06:30.520 --> 06:33.490
- We've been thinking about
having kids for so long.

06:33.560 --> 06:35.688
Just been thinking
about everything

06:35.760 --> 06:37.580
that goes into
being pregnant

06:37.660 --> 06:41.790
and arguing over nursery colours
and organizing a baby shower.

06:41.860 --> 06:43.897
We didn't get to do any of that.

06:43.970 --> 06:45.119
I know, it sounds stupid.

06:45.200 --> 06:46.668
- (Josh and Nora): No, no!

06:46.740 --> 06:48.469
- Not at all!

06:48.540 --> 06:49.803
(Baby babbling)

06:49.870 --> 06:51.838
Why don't you let me
throw you a shower?

06:51.910 --> 06:53.139
- What?

06:53.210 --> 06:54.803
- Yes! I'm throwing
you a shower.

06:54.880 --> 06:56.769
- It's a good idea!
- No!

06:56.850 --> 06:58.841
- No, we've taken
advantage of you already.

06:58.910 --> 07:01.516
- Just give us a couple weeks
to throw it together.

07:01.580 --> 07:03.184
- Seriously?

07:03.250 --> 07:04.888
- Yes, we would love to.

07:06.560 --> 07:08.858
- OK! Thank you!
That'd be great!

07:12.900 --> 07:14.527
- (Nora):
Oh, we're idiots!

07:14.600 --> 07:16.694
We're idiots,
we're idiots, we're idiots!

07:16.770 --> 07:19.068
- Nora, seriously!
It's barely a baby shower.

07:19.130 --> 07:21.861
It's just you, me, alpha Mark
and what's-her-name.

07:21.940 --> 07:23.101
- And her name
is Wendy.

07:23.170 --> 07:24.865
And take it easy on Mark.

07:24.940 --> 07:26.772
- No!
- You've only met him once!

07:26.840 --> 07:27.910
- He's the worst!

07:27.980 --> 07:29.948
He was trying to dominate me!

07:30.010 --> 07:31.739
- No, he wasn't!
- Yes, he was!

07:31.810 --> 07:33.710
- If he tries that here...
- Oh my God!

07:33.780 --> 07:34.713
- What's going on?

07:34.780 --> 07:35.713
- Last minute

07:35.780 --> 07:37.043
werewolf baby shower.

07:37.120 --> 07:40.818
- Well, not exactly last minute.

07:40.890 --> 07:42.881
It's tonight, so...

07:42.960 --> 07:44.724
- That's all right.
I'll clear out.

07:44.790 --> 07:46.724
- No, I was gonna invite you.

07:46.800 --> 07:48.290
- It's OK. I'm
not really up for it.

07:48.360 --> 07:51.523
Nora, actually, have
you talked with Kat?

07:51.600 --> 07:53.898
- Uh, not since
she called to yell at me

07:53.970 --> 07:57.065
and announced that she's
moving out of my apartment.

07:58.870 --> 08:01.100
I think she's broken up
with all of us, Aidan.

08:01.180 --> 08:02.204
(Nora sighing)

08:02.280 --> 08:03.600
- Hey, hey, hey!

08:04.810 --> 08:06.744
Look, I know you're sad, OK?

08:06.820 --> 08:08.811
But I've been thinking
a lot about this

08:08.880 --> 08:16.880
and I want you to look
at it this way:

08:42.419 --> 08:43.909
This is the first time
you've been dumped...

08:43.990 --> 08:45.947
she won't cry before
hanging up the phone.

08:46.020 --> 08:48.910
- Oh, poor lonely boy
and his broken heart.

08:48.990 --> 08:50.151
You're pathetic!

08:50.230 --> 08:52.028
- I know!

08:52.090 --> 08:53.251
- Go see what's-her-name.

08:53.330 --> 08:54.695
- Kick down the door.

08:54.760 --> 08:56.125
- Give her neck
the old snapperoo.

08:56.200 --> 08:58.623
- I mean, that's what
gets you off, right?

08:58.700 --> 09:00.691
That's your--
That's your thing.

09:00.770 --> 09:03.740
- They might have been nice
when they were alive,

09:03.810 --> 09:05.869
but as ghosts, they're
ratched-ass bitches.

09:05.940 --> 09:07.704
They're fine!
- What did you do?

09:07.780 --> 09:10.169
- I banished them
from the house! You're welcome!

09:10.250 --> 09:11.900
- You shouldn't
have done that!

09:11.980 --> 09:13.869
- I couldn't stand
here and watch them

09:13.950 --> 09:15.111
talk to you like that!

09:15.180 --> 09:17.786
- I deserve this.
I really do.

09:17.850 --> 09:19.887
- I guess it doesn't
matter where they are,

09:19.960 --> 09:21.382
because they
couldn't torture you

09:21.460 --> 09:23.019
as much as you
torture yourself!

09:23.090 --> 09:25.787
- You don't understand
what I did, what I am!

09:25.860 --> 09:27.794
That's exactly
what Kat is afraid of.

09:27.860 --> 09:29.294
That is exactly what--

09:30.470 --> 09:31.619
Sally?

09:36.840 --> 09:39.730
- All right, I'm heading out.
Is everything on this list?

09:39.810 --> 09:41.278
- Don't forget the mixed nuts.

09:41.340 --> 09:43.069
- Yeah!
- They're key.

09:43.150 --> 09:45.869
- Can you keep an eye on my
sp--spana--skanakopita?

09:45.950 --> 09:48.339
My, uh, spanako--
spanakopita.

09:48.420 --> 09:52.857
Because phyllo dough
is, like, angel skin.

09:52.920 --> 09:54.115
(Doorbell buzzing)

09:54.190 --> 09:55.851
- Don't say I got
the time wrong.

09:55.920 --> 09:56.921
- No, no.

09:58.260 --> 09:59.921
(Grunting)

10:02.000 --> 10:03.126
- Hey.

10:03.200 --> 10:04.725
- Hi!

10:04.800 --> 10:05.824
(Sighing)

10:05.900 --> 10:07.868
- Guess who's super sober?

10:10.010 --> 10:11.205
(Sighing)

10:14.110 --> 10:15.430
- When did you get out?

10:15.510 --> 10:17.399
- A week and a half ago.

10:17.480 --> 10:18.845
- And you didn't call us?

10:18.910 --> 10:20.674
- I still had
a lot to figure out.

10:20.750 --> 10:22.218
Didn't want to dump that on you,

10:22.280 --> 10:24.089
so I went home
and dumped it on Mom.

10:24.150 --> 10:26.209
- Oh, great! Yeah,
how did that go?

10:26.290 --> 10:28.258
- Well, exactly as well
as you might think.

10:28.320 --> 10:29.788
- Yeah.

10:29.860 --> 10:31.919
- Which is why
I'm here to use you

10:31.990 --> 10:33.424
and your couch.

10:33.500 --> 10:36.026
I just need a place to crash
for a couple of days.

10:36.100 --> 10:37.465
I've got a
studio lined up--

10:37.530 --> 10:39.123
- Of course you're
staying here.

10:39.200 --> 10:40.759
- Thank you.

10:40.840 --> 10:42.968
- After we sprint to
the grocery store real quick.

10:43.040 --> 10:44.769
Do you mind?

10:44.840 --> 10:47.275
- Why am I sprinting?
- We're hosting a baby shower.

10:47.340 --> 10:48.375
- Oh!

10:48.440 --> 10:49.805
- In an hour and a half.

10:49.880 --> 10:50.802
- Oh.

10:50.880 --> 10:51.676
- With champagne.

10:53.380 --> 10:55.371
- We didn't know
you were coming!

10:55.450 --> 10:58.886
- It's OK. It's all good.
I can be around the stuff.

10:58.950 --> 11:00.714
It's a baby shower!

11:00.790 --> 11:03.725
That's a party I can
actually handle. Babies!

11:03.790 --> 11:05.485
- Yeah.

11:05.560 --> 11:08.052
** You told me words *

11:08.130 --> 11:12.124
* That will never expire *

11:14.040 --> 11:16.805
* Watch what my body says *

11:16.870 --> 11:20.408
* When you're caught
being a liar *

11:22.410 --> 11:26.847
*T'll fire words
as staccato sounds *

11:26.920 --> 11:30.185
* Grinding my teeth,
shoulders tightly wound **

11:30.250 --> 11:33.754
- You know, it's a real bad idea
to be following me, Kenny!

11:35.490 --> 11:36.924
(Scoffing, tut-tutting)

11:39.900 --> 11:42.767
- You know, I've been calling
you for over a week now.

11:42.830 --> 11:44.320
Why haven't you
been answering?

11:44.400 --> 11:45.925
- I don't know
where she is.

11:46.000 --> 11:47.832
- What are you talking about?

11:47.900 --> 11:52.133
- The mysterious vampire hunter.
I haven't seen her, all right?

11:52.210 --> 11:54.429
- No, that's...
That's not why I was calling.

11:54.510 --> 11:56.774
I just thought we were...

11:56.850 --> 12:00.047
I don't know,
reconnecting or something.

12:00.120 --> 12:01.440
I just wanted to hang out.

12:02.550 --> 12:05.042
- You caught me on a weird day.

12:06.190 --> 12:08.158
- What is it, junkie stuff?

12:08.220 --> 12:11.155
Roomie stuff?
Romance stuff?

12:13.130 --> 12:14.200
Romance stuff.

12:14.260 --> 12:15.819
- Kat and I broke up.

12:15.900 --> 12:16.867
- So you're what?

12:16.930 --> 12:18.364
You're doing the whole,

12:18.430 --> 12:20.398
"I'm gonna walk around
sad, thinking about her

12:20.470 --> 12:23.030
"while I try not to think
about her," sort of thing?

12:23.110 --> 12:25.306
- What the hell do you
know about it, Kenny?

12:25.370 --> 12:26.872
- Fine, that's a good point.

12:26.940 --> 12:28.578
It's not very easy
to entice a girl

12:28.640 --> 12:31.473
to sit in a hospital and watch
a movie through a glass barrier.

12:33.350 --> 12:35.148
But I have watched
enough television

12:35.220 --> 12:38.190
to know what people deal with
when going through breakups.

12:38.250 --> 12:41.220
- What do people deal with
when going through a breakup?

12:41.290 --> 12:44.555
- Well, I nailed the whole "sad
walk around town," didn't I?

12:44.630 --> 12:46.382
(Scoffing)

12:46.460 --> 12:47.495
Now you got step 2.

12:47.560 --> 12:49.119
- What's step 2?

12:49.200 --> 12:50.998
- Drown your sorrows!

12:51.070 --> 12:53.289
- No, uh-uh. I'm not going
to a blood den, Kenny!

12:53.370 --> 12:54.997
- No, no, no!
You don't have to.

12:55.070 --> 12:57.061
I have got a fridge
packed with bagged stuff.

12:57.140 --> 12:59.029
Just in case you
ever came over.

13:00.340 --> 13:01.432
- Bagged stuff?

13:01.510 --> 13:03.046
- Yes.

13:03.110 --> 13:06.375
(Siren wailing in distance)

13:07.650 --> 13:09.049
Yes!

13:09.120 --> 13:10.042
- Come on!

13:10.120 --> 13:11.485
- OK, I'm coming!

13:15.320 --> 13:17.584
- She's so cute!

13:17.660 --> 13:19.321
Look at those cheekies!

13:19.390 --> 13:21.290
- I know!

13:21.360 --> 13:22.498
- And she's a werewolf?

13:22.560 --> 13:24.494
- Just like the rest of us!

13:26.630 --> 13:30.510
- I didn't mean that
to sound like an insult.

13:30.570 --> 13:35.030
I'm an alcoholic. I have no
idea why I said that either.

13:35.110 --> 13:36.339
- Champagne?

13:36.410 --> 13:37.809
- Yes!

13:38.680 --> 13:40.614
(Knocking on door)

13:40.680 --> 13:44.218
- Josh, there is something
I should tell you. I...

13:44.290 --> 13:45.314
- Hi!
Hey!

13:45.390 --> 13:46.983
- Welcome! Come on in!

13:47.060 --> 13:48.619
Look at
that present!

13:48.690 --> 13:50.055
- (Wendy):
Hi, everybody!

13:50.130 --> 13:52.451
- Wow! You brought
a big, big gift.

13:52.530 --> 13:55.090
- It's just a little something
for the new parents.

13:55.160 --> 14:00.234
- Yeah, and you brought 2 cases
of beer and 2 other couples.

14:00.300 --> 14:03.008
- More on the way.
Nothing to worry about.

14:03.070 --> 14:04.435
They're like us. It's cool.

14:04.510 --> 14:06.205
- Is it though, Mark?

14:06.270 --> 14:08.409
- Of course!
Of course it's cool.

14:08.480 --> 14:10.278
It's, you know,
the more the merrier!

14:10.350 --> 14:13.012
Uh, let's find
