(Gasping)

28:13.520 --> 28:15.852
- Hey, Henry!

28:15.920 --> 28:20.426
Oh, this old bird's tough,
but she's worth the work!

28:20.490 --> 28:23.926
(Both laughing)

28:32.140 --> 28:34.006
- There she is!

28:34.080 --> 28:36.378
Hey, sweetheart,
first you bail on me,

28:36.440 --> 28:39.478
and then Kenny wanders off,
and I have no idea where he--

28:39.550 --> 28:41.473
Are you OK?

28:41.550 --> 28:43.882
- Yeah, I was in the '20s.

28:43.950 --> 28:44.940
- No way! The '20s!

28:45.020 --> 28:46.545
That's some good music,

28:46.620 --> 28:48.156
and the speakeasies!

28:48.220 --> 28:49.517
- Something's not right!

28:49.590 --> 28:51.080
When I use the magic,

28:51.160 --> 28:52.924
I'm gone a few minutes,
maybe an hour.

28:52.990 --> 28:55.550
But tonight, 2 days,
and now 2 weeks.

28:55.630 --> 28:57.394
- Oh my God, quantum leap!

28:57.460 --> 29:01.340
- Aidan, just listen! What
if I can't get myself out?

29:01.400 --> 29:03.198
I can't use spells there.

29:03.270 --> 29:05.261
What if I'm
stuck there forever?

29:05.340 --> 29:08.435
- OK, listen. I don't care
about time travel or magic.

29:08.510 --> 29:10.069
I just wanna get with you.

29:12.510 --> 29:14.547
That was awkward.
- I'm gonna walk off now.

29:14.620 --> 29:16.247
Yeah, away...
from you.

29:16.320 --> 29:17.242
- OK.

29:32.430 --> 29:35.468
- Hey, Aidan's
inappropriately young friend!

29:35.540 --> 29:38.601
Do your parents even care
that you're going to strip clubs

29:38.670 --> 29:40.604
and getting hammered
with werewolves?

29:40.670 --> 29:42.479
Do you even have parents?

29:42.540 --> 29:46.101
- It's not for me. It's for
a girl, a very pretty girl.

29:46.180 --> 29:47.341
Her name is Astrid.

29:47.410 --> 29:49.048
- Of course it is.

29:49.120 --> 29:50.986
- Astrid, there's
no more ale.

29:51.050 --> 29:53.382
Do you want a lager instead?
- Sure.

29:53.450 --> 29:56.488
- All right,
lager it is.

29:56.560 --> 29:59.120
- Oh my God! Your face!

29:59.190 --> 30:02.558
- No, no, no! It's OK, it's OK!
Just look at me! Look at me!

30:02.630 --> 30:04.359
Listen to me!
- Josh, help!

30:04.430 --> 30:07.491
- Hey! What the hell's going on?
- Nothing. I'm sorry.

30:07.570 --> 30:11.063
- His face... I didn't know what
he was. I don't know what he is!

30:11.140 --> 30:12.210
- What were you doing?

30:12.270 --> 30:13.362
- I was getting a beer.

30:13.440 --> 30:14.635
That's it. I promise.

30:14.710 --> 30:16.269
- But you don't
drink beer, do you?

30:16.340 --> 30:17.501
- Hey! Leave him alone.

30:17.580 --> 30:18.650
- Stay out of this.

30:18.710 --> 30:20.303
- It's a misunderstanding.

30:20.380 --> 30:21.518
Let's hear him out, OK?

30:21.580 --> 30:23.218
- We know what he was up to.

30:23.280 --> 30:24.987
- Everybody,
just calm down, OK?

30:25.050 --> 30:27.246
- I think we should
get the baby some place safe.

30:27.320 --> 30:28.879
- I wasn't
gonna drink her, OK?

30:28.960 --> 30:30.257
- What?
- I swear.

30:30.320 --> 30:32.186
- Someone get something
sharp and wooden.

30:33.430 --> 30:34.454
- Get off me!
- Hey!

30:34.530 --> 30:36.225
- Josh, you gotta hear me out.

30:36.300 --> 30:37.324
(Both grunting)

30:37.400 --> 30:39.164
(Bone cracking,
screaming)

30:39.230 --> 30:40.265
- Kenny!

30:42.200 --> 30:43.599
(Both grunting)

30:43.670 --> 30:45.263
No!

30:46.740 --> 30:48.208
(Grunting)

30:50.580 --> 30:51.604
- No, I got this!

30:52.710 --> 30:54.519
(Both grunting)

30:54.580 --> 30:56.412
(Both grunting)

30:56.480 --> 30:58.448
- (Josh):
Aidan, stop!

30:58.520 --> 31:01.353
(Both grunting)

31:02.590 --> 31:04.649
Aidan, get him!

31:04.730 --> 31:07.358
- No, no, no, no, no!

31:07.430 --> 31:09.398
- I didn't even do anything!

31:09.460 --> 31:11.167
- (Aidan): Come on!
- Sorry!

31:11.230 --> 31:12.561
(Groaning)

31:14.170 --> 31:15.990
(Breathing heavily)

31:18.770 --> 31:22.377
- That kid is supposed
to represent the peace?

31:22.440 --> 31:26.570
- It was a mistake, Mark!
Kenny wasn't gonna do anything!

31:26.650 --> 31:29.620
- He's a time bomb, Josh.
And you know it.

31:29.680 --> 31:31.341
- Caroline, don't.

31:31.420 --> 31:33.616
- I'm sorry, Josh, but
after what happened here,

31:33.690 --> 31:36.318
it's pretty obvious
we need to stick together.

31:36.390 --> 31:37.357
- Let's go.

31:37.420 --> 31:38.649
- Andrew...

31:41.630 --> 31:43.029
(Sobbing)

31:46.170 --> 31:48.093
(Insects chirping)

31:50.540 --> 31:51.939
- Is Emily OK?

31:54.810 --> 31:56.733
- I don't know.
I really don't.

31:56.810 --> 31:59.279
- Josh, I have to
tell you something.

31:59.350 --> 32:01.978
(Inhaling deeply)

32:02.050 --> 32:05.418
- It was you, wasn't it? You
did--you did something to her.

32:05.490 --> 32:07.083
You made her see something?

32:07.150 --> 32:08.686
- Yeah.
- Oh my God.

32:08.760 --> 32:10.649
- I'm really sorry.
She was so alone.

32:10.720 --> 32:12.427
I wanted her to see me.

32:12.490 --> 32:14.197
I wanted her to speak to me.

32:14.260 --> 32:15.694
(Inhaling deeply)

32:17.100 --> 32:18.226
- OK.

32:18.300 --> 32:19.529
- Please don't
walk away.

32:19.600 --> 32:21.238
- I don't understand.
- I'm sorry!

32:21.300 --> 32:23.496
I wanted to help! She
needed somebody to talk to.

32:23.570 --> 32:26.130
- I know your intentions
were good. I'm sure,

32:26.210 --> 32:28.406
They always are, but...

32:28.480 --> 32:32.269
Let's just forget
the deep, deep damage

32:32.350 --> 32:34.375
that you leave behind.

32:34.450 --> 32:36.111
(Sighing)

32:36.180 --> 32:38.387
It's not all you.
It's just, it's...

32:39.850 --> 32:41.454
It's been a long night.

32:43.620 --> 32:44.758
I'm gonna go to bed.

32:44.830 --> 32:47.128
- I can help her.
I can help Emily.

32:48.260 --> 32:49.455
- How?

32:49.530 --> 32:51.259
- I know that
I have to be careful

32:51.330 --> 32:52.559
about how
I use the magic,

32:52.630 --> 32:55.133
because there are
growing consequences.

32:55.200 --> 32:57.339
But there are spells
that I can try on Emily,

32:57.400 --> 32:58.538
spells that curb cravings

32:58.610 --> 33:01.602
or to make her
forget about tonight.

33:01.680 --> 33:03.307
I owe her that.

33:04.410 --> 33:06.071
- After everything...

33:08.180 --> 33:10.740
I-I'm gonna
call it a night.

33:14.720 --> 33:16.051
- Hey.

33:16.120 --> 33:17.190
- Hey.

33:17.260 --> 33:18.523
- How's Emily?

33:18.590 --> 33:20.684
- Oh God! Um...

33:22.230 --> 33:23.220
White-knuckled?

33:23.300 --> 33:24.324
(Sighing)

33:24.400 --> 33:26.198
- Is there anything I can do?

33:26.270 --> 33:30.389
- Yeah, you can lay here
and feel useless with me.

33:30.470 --> 33:31.631
(Sighing)

33:31.710 --> 33:32.734
- God, what a night!

33:32.810 --> 33:34.278
- Mmm, tell me about it.

33:34.340 --> 33:36.229
(Sighing)

33:36.310 --> 33:39.610
- I was just thinking
about Andrew and Caroline

33:39.680 --> 33:41.648
and the whole pack thing.

33:43.520 --> 33:45.113
I get it.

33:46.450 --> 33:48.452
They want their
baby to be safe.

33:49.520 --> 33:51.124
<i>- I know.</i>

33:51.190 --> 33:55.195
If we had a kid, I would
do anything to protect him.

33:58.370 --> 34:00.225
- Yeah, it's important to...

34:01.700 --> 34:04.067
feel like you
belong somewhere...

34:05.540 --> 34:07.668
have that,
you know, strength...

34:08.880 --> 34:10.632
that you get with family.

34:11.850 --> 34:13.806
- We have a family, though...

34:16.219 --> 34:18.813
Aidan, Sally, Emily.

34:20.550 --> 34:22.813
They're beyond dysfunctional

34:22.889 --> 34:27.452
and I wanna smother them
with a pillow half the time,

34:27.530 --> 34:29.418
but they're our family.

34:31.429 --> 34:33.467
- You know what I mean.

34:33.530 --> 34:34.793
- Yeah.

34:40.639 --> 34:42.301
Good night!

34:43.480 --> 34:44.800
- Good night.

34:46.750 --> 34:51.380
(Siren wailing in distance)

34:51.449 --> 34:53.543
** Cut your cards *

34:53.620 --> 34:58.729
* Burn the letters
you were given *

34:58.790 --> 35:02.226
* In every word,
they swore... *

35:02.300 --> 35:04.268
- Kat, I need to talk--

35:04.330 --> 35:06.298
- No! Stop it,
you're scaring me!

35:06.370 --> 35:07.963
- We need to talk.

35:10.940 --> 35:12.465
- Come inside.

35:12.540 --> 35:15.874
* And children... *

35:15.940 --> 35:17.578
- I love you.

35:18.810 --> 35:21.450
And I need you to love me.

35:22.720 --> 35:24.779
- I love you, Aidan.

35:24.850 --> 35:27.342
- Forever.

35:27.420 --> 35:29.479
I want you to
be with me forever.

35:29.560 --> 35:32.860
- Of course. Forever.

35:32.930 --> 35:35.649
* Then you would howl *

35:35.730 --> 35:39.769
* Down that road *

35:39.830 --> 35:43.539
* Where all your brothers *

35:43.600 --> 35:48.470
* And your sisters wouldn't go *

35:48.540 --> 35:51.976
* Dream of girls *

35:52.050 --> 35:57.580
* That made you feel 15 *

35:57.650 --> 36:00.517
* With the palest skin *

36:00.590 --> 36:04.288
* And her mother's sympathy *

36:04.360 --> 36:08.524
* But that trail
remains unseen **

36:19.340 --> 36:23.709
-I am. I'm...
gonna crash with a friend.

36:23.780 --> 36:25.748
- You know, you don't
have to leave.

36:25.810 --> 36:28.245
- Yeah, I--I kind of do.

36:28.320 --> 36:30.015
- Listen, last
night, it--it--

36:30.080 --> 36:32.310
That kind of thing
never happens!

36:32.390 --> 36:33.516
It's not like that!

36:33.590 --> 36:36.389
It rarely
happens here.

36:36.460 --> 36:38.349
- Maybe so, but...

36:39.990 --> 36:43.756
Look, it--it's like every time
I'm around, things go haywire.

36:43.830 --> 36:45.696
And there was a time where,

36:45.770 --> 36:48.762
I don't know, I might
have rolled with that,

36:48.840 --> 36:50.899
but--but now I've
gotta admit to myself,

36:50.970 --> 36:52.734
I'm too fragile
to roll with anything.

36:52.810 --> 36:55.529
- I knew it. I knew as soon
as you found out about me.

36:55.610 --> 36:57.578
I knew it would
eventually push you away.

36:57.640 --> 36:58.573
- Josh...

36:59.710 --> 37:01.542
I love you.

37:01.620 --> 37:04.419
And I'll love you
no matter what you are.

37:04.490 --> 37:07.585
But this is
about me, what I am.

37:08.920 --> 37:10.456
- OK.

37:18.060 --> 37:20.290
- This isn't goodbye.
- I know.

37:21.400 --> 37:22.435
- Goodbye.

37:22.500 --> 37:23.535
(Laughing)

37:36.880 --> 37:38.075
(Aidan sighing)

37:41.120 --> 37:45.921
- Wow! How has Josh not
freaked out and cleaned up yet?

37:45.990 --> 37:47.685
(Sniffing)

37:47.760 --> 37:49.956
- He's dealing
with Emily stuff.

37:52.170 --> 37:56.368
- Oh! Right,
yeah. Is she OK?

37:56.440 --> 37:58.363
- Yeah, she's gonna be fine.

37:58.440 --> 38:00.568
- Do you have, like,
a cleaning spell?

38:00.640 --> 38:04.372
You know, maybe get, like, a
broom to dance across the floor.

38:04.450 --> 38:06.077
- Yeah, you know,

38:06.150 --> 38:08.949
I'm really gonna try to pick
my spots with the magic stuff.

38:09.020 --> 38:11.079
I'm afraid of getting
stuck in the past

38:11.150 --> 38:12.811
and witnessing terrible stuff,

38:12.890 --> 38:15.018
like my friends
murdering innocent people

38:15.090 --> 38:16.057
like it's a game.

38:17.160 --> 38:18.525
- Hold on,

38:18.590 --> 38:20.388
you said something
about the '20s,

38:20.460 --> 38:22.349
that you were
with me in the '20s.

38:22.430 --> 38:24.057
Were you with me in the '20s?

38:25.670 --> 38:27.092
Oh no!

38:27.170 --> 38:29.798
No, Sally, that was
just such a long time ago!

38:29.870 --> 38:32.362
- You were laughing
while you did it!

38:32.440 --> 38:34.329
One time you were singing!

38:35.440 --> 38:36.976
I always knew you killed, Aidan.

38:37.040 --> 38:39.702
I just had no idea
how much you enjoyed it.

38:39.780 --> 38:43.410
I could have told you that last
night, but you didn't care.

38:43.480 --> 38:45.790
You were just trying
to "get with me."

38:45.850 --> 38:47.113
- Oh!

38:47.190 --> 38:48.954
- I could really
milk this, you know.

38:49.020 --> 38:51.455
I could make you cringe
whenever I wanted to!

38:51.530 --> 38:52.725
- Yes, you could.

38:52.790 --> 38:54.997
- I'm gonna give you
a pass, though,

38:55.060 --> 38:58.394
because you're going
through a rough patch.

38:58.470 --> 39:02.759
But honestly, Aidan, after
spending time with the old you,

39:02.840 --> 39:06.538
I wonder if you don't deserve
to go through this pain.

39:06.610 --> 39:07.907
More, even.

39:07.970 --> 39:09.802
(Sighing)

39:09.880 --> 39:12.872
I don't like when
you lose control.

39:12.950 --> 39:15.578
- Look, you have
to know that that...

39:17.020 --> 39:19.114
it isn't who I am.

39:19.190 --> 39:20.817
That guy from the past --

39:20.890 --> 39:22.710
that guy from last night --

39:22.790 --> 39:24.451
that--that isn't me.

39:24.530 --> 39:26.680
(Sighs)

39:26.760 --> 39:28.819
- I always wondered
why you tried so hard

39:28.900 --> 39:30.459
to do the right thing.

39:30.530 --> 39:33.693
Now I know what you were
trying to make up for.

39:36.570 --> 39:38.607
You're a good man.

39:39.940 --> 39:41.476
Please stay that way.

39:45.550 --> 39:47.507
(Car horns honking)

39:47.580 --> 39:49.912
(* Autumn All the Time
by Sugarplastic *)

39:49.980 --> 39:53.746
** I said hello to you *

39:57.060 --> 39:59.757
* It's all or nothing **

40:01.130 --> 40:03.849
- (Kenny): Hey!
- Hey!

40:03.930 --> 40:06.024
- Hair of the dog?
- Um...

40:06.100 --> 40:08.159
- Wait, that's not
offensive, is it?

40:08.230 --> 40:09.698
- I'm not sure.

40:09.770 --> 40:11.829
- It looks like
the night worked out

40:11.910 --> 40:13.162
for some of us.

40:13.240 --> 40:15.504
- Oh, uh, Astrid, Aidan.
Aidan, Astrid.

40:15.580 --> 40:16.900
- Hey!
- Hi!

40:16.980 --> 40:19.142
What about every other night?

40:19.210 --> 40:21.042
Are you ready for
the flack you'll catch

40:21.110 --> 40:22.180
from both sides?

40:22.250 --> 40:23.615
- Well, Astrid's above

40:23.680 --> 40:24.943
all that gang war stuff.

40:25.020 --> 40:28.217
Besides, she's worth
the flack.

40:28.290 --> 40:30.850
Anyways, um,
you know the memory thing?

40:30.920 --> 40:33.059
I can still do that,
if you really want to.

40:33.130 --> 40:35.690
You know, wipe Kat
right out of your head?

40:35.760 --> 40:37.819
- Uh, thank you, I'm good.

40:37.900 --> 40:39.789
- You sure?
- Yeah.

40:39.870 --> 40:42.032
I think this breakup...

40:43.940 --> 40:47.729
Well, it's the cleanest split
that I've ever had.

40:47.810 --> 40:50.507
I mean, no one disappeared,

40:50.580 --> 40:53.709
no one died
or turned to dust.

40:53.780 --> 40:55.714
You know, it's just normal...

40:55.780 --> 40:56.941
(Snickers)

40:57.020 --> 40:59.182
...human.

40:59.250 --> 41:01.560
- You were in_
a lot of pain last night.

41:01.620 --> 41:03.179
- Yeah.

41:03.260 --> 41:05.683
And I think I need to
carry that pain around with me,

41:05.760 --> 41:06.750
for a little while.

41:16.140 --> 41:17.960
- Yeah.

41:18.040 --> 41:20.668
I just hope it's not too chilly
in the morning, you know?

41:20.740 --> 41:21.969
Hey...

41:22.040 --> 41:23.906
Is--is this
the worst idea ever?

41:23.980 --> 41:25.709
I mean, what are
we doing?

41:25.780 --> 41:27.544
I mean, should we leave?

41:27.610 --> 41:30.944
These people--
- These people need us, Josh.

41:31.020 --> 41:32.181
OK?

41:32.250 --> 41:34.116
It's up to us
to help them.

41:34.190 --> 41:36.181
We can do this.

41:40.890 --> 41:42.028
- Yeah, OK.

41:52.170 --> 41:56.175
- Hey! You guys made it!
Welcome.

41:59.910 --> 42:01.071
- Hey...

42:02.650 --> 42:04.118
I feel like
I owe you an apology

42:04.180 --> 42:06.683
for what happened
at your place.

42:06.750 --> 42:08.957
Things kind of
got out of hand.

42:10.060 --> 42:11.585
I just wanna make sure

42:11.660 --> 42:13.219
that you guys
wanna be here.

42:15.760 --> 42:17.228
- Yeah.

42:19.300 --> 42:21.894
- Great. We're happy
to have you.

42:21.970 --> 42:23.631
Let's do it!

42:23.700 --> 42:26.965
(* Man singing pop,
lyrics indistinct *)

42:38.820 --> 42:38.888
Closed Captions: Vision Globale
